## ❗ Problem Being Solved

Background artists in a typical 2D animation studio spend an average of 8 hours per background manually painting detailed environments from scratch.

In a mid-sized studio producing 20 episodes per season with an average of 12 unique backgrounds per episode, this generates ~1,920 hours of repetitive detailing work per season — for one studio alone.
**Pain points addressed:**
- Implied locations buried in action lines missed during manual reads
- Mood and atmosphere notes inconsistently captured across supervisors
- No standardised format — every supervisor extracts differently
- New artists can't independently interpret vague scene directions
---

## ⚡ Automation Potential

**Level: High**

| Dimension | Assessment |
|-----------|------------|
| Repetitiveness | Very high — same structure every time |
| Data availability | All placeholders exist in HRIS |
| Human judgment needed | Low — tone review only |
| Integration possibility | Could trigger automatically from HRIS workflow |
| Estimated time saving | ~80% (45 min → ~8 min including review) |

**Human-in-the-loop role:** HR coordinator reads output, checks placeholders resolved correctly, and clicks send. No rewriting expected at v1.2.

**Scaling note:** A chain of 10 stores hiring 4/month = 480 emails/year. Automation saves approximately **324 hours annually** at current manual rate.

---

## ⚠️ Risks and Limitations

| Risk | Level | Mitigation |
|------|-------|------------|
| Hallucination if placeholders are empty or malformed | Medium | Validate all fields in HRIS before prompt runs. System should reject prompt if any placeholder is null. |
| Generic or impersonal output despite personalisation | Low | v1.2 testing shows this is rare; coordinator review catches it |
| Confidential data included accidentally | Low | Prompt explicitly excludes salary/contract terms; HRIS integration should not pass financial fields |
| Tone mismatch for unusual roles (e.g. senior management hire) | Low | This prompt is scoped to frontline retail roles only. Senior hires use a separate template. |

**Overall risk rating: LOW** — suitable for near-full automation with lightweight human review.

